summary:
The Security Council:

Recalling previous resolutions and statements on Yemen, including resolutions 2624 (2022) and 2675 (2023),

Reaffirming commitment to Yemen's unity, sovereignty, independence, and territorial integrity,

Determining the situation in Yemen remains a threat to international peace and security,

Acting under Chapter VII of the UN Charter,

1. Renews measures imposed by paragraphs 11 and 15 of resolution 2140 (2014) until 15 November 2024, reaffirms provisions of paragraphs 12, 13, 14, and 16 of resolution 2140 (2014), and paragraphs 14 to 17 of resolution 2216 (2015);

2. Extends the Panel of Experts' mandate until 15 December 2024, and requests the Secretary-General to re-establish the Panel, in consultation with the Committee, to provide a midterm update by 15 April 2024, and a final report by 15 October 2024;

3. Requests the Panel to provide updates and a final report as specified;

4. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
